f the last starbases of the farthest system... but there she is! (at least for my random generated game).Music:The game ost is really good. The compositor is Christopher Robert Adams and besides the good of his work, the game allows you to customize the directory of each kind of music (exploration,combat...) and you can put there your own ost.I, for exemple, have been listening  Cowboy Beebop.if you want to listen the ost take a look at this linkhttps://www.reddit.com/r/RebelGalaxy/comments/3pe3xg/rebel_galaxy_soundtrack_double_damage_games_a/http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=804045352Story:It's... simple but enought to do your way through the system, exploring, fighting, trading, and improving over and over your ship. From a little old carrier to the most powerfull destructor... don't expect much more.Take a look at the shipshttp://rebelgalaxy.gamepedia.com/ShipsGameplay:I recommend to use a gamepad.And here comes the controversial point... Rebel Galaxy is a 2D space game. Besides, is single player and always in 3rd person (ship) view.   I could compare it to a naval ship combat, with cannons and lateral combat, where you have to change your flank because your enemy will sunk you if you continue on that side.It could be nasty, even an insult for those who think on space games like Elite or Star Citizen but damn... it's fun! I really enjoyed it, it has it's strategic point and you can be quickly destroyed if you rush into an enemy formation that you think that are weak.So, if you can look forward beyond games like ED or SC, you will enjoy it.One interesting thing. The entire game is redone each time you play, the connections of each system with another, the planets each system has, the type of planet, well, everything. You will play into a new universe each time you start a game.Space:The way you travel through system is using jumpgates, and it's instant travel. You can only navigate and explore each system, and to balance that, each system is really alive. Each time you travel from A point to B point, you will find something, let's say: traders convoys, pirates, milita ships, emergency beacons, space trash, nebulas, asteroid field, ice field, debris from older battles, a lot of stations from the different factions and planets, satellites which you can hack to get information... and more.In this game, space is old. Humanity has spread all over the place and thousands of years of races activity, has changed it and let their legacy. while you navigate you will see little pieces of  trash around your ship and if you destroy a big ship and you come back days later, you will find the debris.Modshttp://steamcommunity.com/app/290300/discussions/2/405691491120297253/This mod will change some important things, add new ships to be able to use and rebalance others. Please read the description to be sure if you want to use it. Thanks to Timberrino for the link to this mod.Negative point:The cloned facesThere are few mods.The repetitive missions."
