76561198046426560,Not Recommended,290300,31448074,Posted: 29 April,all,hack.causality,"Pros:  Combat is fun, controls are tight and polished, sound design is excellent.Cons: There's not a lot to DO with the excellent gameplay you're given.  Many of the ships have specs that make them garbage you would never fly, even high-end ships.  There are only three mission variants:  go kill things in a giant blob, go kill things distributed in a circle, go kill things around a station and then blow up bits of the station.  Exploration is non-existent, the only differences between systems is the color of the star and the HP/damage of the NPCs.  Flying around is more like eve-online than Freelancer, in that there are small bubbles of content separated by vast gulfs of empty space you warp through at blinding speed.  You will never fly through an asteroid field or gas cloud for pleasure in this game.The story is good but incredibly short.  I spent hours between story missions grinding and was still only halfway through the ship tree when the story just ended.  In traditional storytelling we were at the point of a minor climax before a setback leading to the final climax and triumph when the story just ends, so setback, no drama, just over.There's also zero exposition or world-building. The only things you learn about alien species you have to glean from their ship designs.  You never find out the history of this world or its politics or how and what Earth is doing.It feels like this was originally going to be a much larger game but the devs ran out of time.  The unrealized potential disappoints me."
