,Recommended,290300,30346163,Posted: 5 March,all,BonesMoses,"Though it has its shortcomings in the story arena, it's really an excuse to join the upgrade treadmill in buying the biggest, nastiest, blow-things-up-est ship you can manage. It's all about playing missions to get money and buy those sweet, sweet weapons and armor upgrades until you have a veritable capital-ship erasing fortress. At the end of the game, I spent a good couple hours just annihilating missions for giggles; very fun!And a hint if you plan on playing this on easy mode: join the Merchant Guild ASAP. Equip your ship with Null-Grav Boosters. Occasionally they'll have a mission that's worth like 10x the average mission price because you're supposed to obtain materials and deliver them through a blockade. Obtain them by going to the Commodity Market and looking at which station supplies them. Go to that station, buy their stock, and exit the game. When you continue, they'll have restocked. Keep doing that until you have the necessary units, then deliver to the target station. About 30sm from the location, you'll get pulled out of warp. Just engage your boosters and tap deflectors when rockets are about to hit you or you need to recharge the booster. The first time I did this, I made $250k when missions in the area were only $20-30k, and I wish I knew about it way earlier."
