,Not Recommended,290300,18639022,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,Equinox,"Its unfortunate as the game has so much potential, but in reality is nothing but one big grind.It basicly goes like this, you do a story mission, then you have to grind for hours doing repetitive missions to gain new gear after which you can do another story mission and have to grind for hours again.When you finaly get the baddest ship in the system the story progresses to the next system and it all starts over again.The praised music is nice, but it does get repetitve too when you play for a few hours, its like a cd on repeat all the time.It also bothers me that this game is clearly made to be played with a controller and not with mouse/keyboard.Aiming is done with the mouse on a 2d plane, but in all modes but broadside the crosshair snaps on targets so there is very little manual aiming to be done.You simply select a target and click the mouse to fire the weapons group.Seeing the crosshairs snap your constantly moving you mouse to try and get it to snap on the target you want it.On a controller this isnt a problem as you just move the analog stick, but a mouse doesnt move infinite.Ironicly you cant aim up as everything happens in a 2d plane, but small strike craft do fly over you.Its also not possible to assign weapon groups, the groups are assigned automaticly by the type of weapon used.They are ordenance, projectile and beams, its not possible to manualy fire a mixed selection, you can only control one at a time with the number keys, they others are ai controlled.The game does have allot of good pointers though, the graphics are awesome, the mood is good, its casual and laid back.AI turret control can be set to your preferences, like shooting only selected or target only small craft.There is a large selection of ships and weapons to be had, which gives allot of variation in tactics.The ships are clearly a progression over eachother though, they dont give you room to select multiple ships of a same strength, the next ship in line is always more expensive, and somewhat better than the last, yet requiring a different tactic.Pro's:Great graphicsGood moodVery casualGreat controller supportSomewhat intrigueing storyCons:Allot of grinding requiredRepetitive missionsPoor mous/keyboard support, fixed mouse ballisticWeapon groups are fixed, no buttons to fire other weapons than the ones selectedLooking back, i may not have bought this."
