76561198053874177,Recommended,290300,20486027,"Posted: 12 January, 2016",all,MTB-Fritz,"Rebel Galax ReviewI want to start out with a rough outline of the game. Rebel Galaxy is an action oriented spaceship game. Its NOT a simulator and its NOT a strategy game. The developers last title was Torchlight II and they managed to pack the ARPGs elements into this game as well. Theres loot theres upgrades, lots of ships and all this in a space setting which looks beautifull.So....action oriented Space game.Who are you in this game?You are a young starship captain and you dont start your carreer in a space fighter either. You start out with a frigatte. Sure its small and doesnt have a whole lot to it but its in the capital ship class and thats what all other flyable ships are as well. Capital ships. From the measly frigatte to the mighty dreadnaught. You will curse the bombers, fighters and gunships all around you but you ll never fly them yourself. And why would you? The weapons you have at your disposal are frightening and extremly destructive.The game drops you in front of a Space station and your ""campaign"" is to find your aunt which vanished and is rumored to ve run into some trouble while following her not-so-white activities. Your ship has all the things you need to set off and start playing but pretty much everything is crap...at first.Lets be clear about something.....when you ""fly"" your ship you ll do it on a 2D plane only. No fancy going ""up"" or ""down"" with such a large ship. You can only turn left or right and increase or reduce thrust.On the other hand you are given your hull, armor on top and a shield generator to protect yourself from other big ships and small ones alike. In order to defend your newbie hide you have 3 weapon categories with multiple weapon choices in each being your Broadsides, your secondaries and your turrets. And here is where the game ""hooks"" you (or not) with its addictive elements. Pretty much every station offers a wide variety of modules in different qualities (starting at Mark 1 going to Mark 6) and in order to being able to buy these lil babies you gonna need a lot of credits. Sadly credits dont come around on their own so you got to chose from a list of activities in order to EARN credits until you can afford the next upgrade.Mining, treasure hunting, bounty hunting, guild missions, cargo missions, combat missions, escort missions. This game offers a wide variety of things you can do. You ll still do it all on your ship of course but with the right pick of modules you can ""specialize"" your ship to certain mission types.Missions vary in difficulty based on your total worth and the opposition you ll encounter. Gear apart ""how"" you fly has a big impact on your survivability as well which is a nice touch IMO.The flow of the game.Your playground is a star system with all its gas clouds, asteroid belts, planets and other space farers you can encounter. Each system is several AUs big and once you upgrade your engines (seperate module) you ll be able to visit other star systems which makes the whole picture bigger. Star systems offer different tiers of servces and challenges meaning in order to get the higher Mark modules you ll need to switch to different systems which are populated by harder enemies so this is the circle you face in RG. Upgrade to be able to do harder stuff which in turn leads to better upgrades etc.System to system travel is done via ""jump gates"" which are an instant switch. In-system you rely on your trusted warp engines to get you from A to B. The whole system is easy to understand and easier to use and it ensures that you can jump into RG for 15-20 minutes at a time and get things done. Yes missions are short affairs but nevertheless they can be engaging and entertaining.Rebel Galaxy looks lovely. Its overall colorfull and the default music track I would describe as ""cowboys in space"" but hell....it fits.Its easy to use and hard to master. Upgrading to a new ship is always a big moment and find myself ""itching"" wanting to try it out. I dumped a whole lot of hours into this game simply because its FUN. Its not overall realistic and it could use some more complexity but its a cheap title made by 2 people. What you get for your money is AAA material in my book.I play several saves at the moment because the game allows you to take speific paths which dont go well with other paths so decisions need to be worked on and are really hard to lift once done. For example I have a save where I aligned myself with the pirate factions so most stations fire on sight, I m a wanted criminal by the militia and traders dont trade with me anymore. On the other hand I can pillage and loot whatever I find, spit on enemy militia destroyers and smuggle with illegal subtsnces to my hearts desire. Also there are some ""pirate-only"" ships and modules I can aquire this way.The same is true for a military career. You ll be hunting pirates mostly and will be a respected captain in most corners of the galaxy. Some militia-only ships taunt you in case you are not doing all this out of your heart.Its kind of a ""short"" game. You have your storyline which brings you to mid game I d say after that the open game starts which is the whole galaxy with you dumped in the middle. From then on you gonna have to find your own goals sandbox style. Eventually you ll run out of ships to switch and modules to upgrade and will swim in credits. Thats when you ll notice your motivation to drop. Either you drop by from time to time to enjoy a mission or you start over. Apart from the storyline which is always the same you can pick fromseveral different approaches in the game which are all viably.I certainly dont play as much as I used to anymore but its still fun and to be honest, I consider it a good purchase....never regretted shelling out the cash (and for such a title thats actually cheap)9/10"
76561197968331161,Recommended,290300,28545187,"Posted: 22 December, 2016",all,Danger,"So I've Hit the 50 hour threshold with this game.  I find it hard to have a negative reveiw for something I put so much time into, So its positive now.Pros:Good musicGood graphicsSolid progression systemOpen world with the ability to choose what you want to do to progressCons:Simplistic combatHighly repetiveMeh main plotlineSome early parts i found very frustrating and had to save scum to get past itSo orginally i didn't like this game.  But what i failed to realize was that this isn't a game you sit down and play for hours on end.  Its a game you play for a bit then come back the next day or so.  Thats what got me I just kept coming back.Also I only spent $6 on it that might have helped.Space pirates/traders/anti pirates unite!"
