76561197983740996,Recommended,290300,31610273,Posted: 7 May,all,Chane,"Six days ago you received a cryptic message form your aunt Juno, the family black sheep, who you haven't seen or heard from in over ten years. The message provided access codes to the Rasputin, a small, outdated space craft and the demand to meet her at a remote space station with a questionable reputation.This is the beginning of your adventure, that takes you through 14 different systems, each huge and filled with quests. In this open world you can either follow the main story or venture off to become a pirate, a mercenary, a trader or a rouge that only follows his own rules.Accept missions to make money and upgrade your weapons, equipment and ships. Smuggle illegal wares or break through sieges. Mine asteroid fields or transport valuable goods while being chased by aliens and pirates. Visit various different space stations and hire mercenaries to fight along your side.Rebel Galaxy is an action game that's best played with a controller. It's a Freelancer clone that pulls it's addiction from the urge to permanently improve your ship and equipment to stand against your various enemies.Space feels very alive in this game and the different groups form a plausible social society. The biggest achievement of the developers is the balancing of the space fights. The combination of broadsides, turrets, shields, deflectors and hull types gives this game a fantastic balance. Either if you have a tiny weak ship, like at the start of the game, or a huge dreadnought, you always have a chance to survive and pull out of a fight and at the same time can never be sure you won't be defeated. Only after about 35 hours into the game and about 50 million credits richer, will you reach a point, where you feel overpowered. Given the fact that enemies don't adapt to your strength, this is a huge achievement.Pros:- good story- good music- great space battles- fights are very well balanced- different alien races- highly addictive- very good controls (with controller)- many different weapon types- different defence systems- many different ships- different ship types from different groups- alien weapons- easy docking process- traders, mercenaries, pirates, militia, religious fanatics, aliensCons:- very repetitive (but in an addictive way)- some achievements are bugged- too many meteoroid and scrap fields- warp travel is far too often interrupted by stellar mass- mining is boring"
