76561197970753965,Recommended,290300,21532684,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,Fuzzba11,"Love being a space cowboy in Rebel Galaxy, it just feels good to fly around and fight other ships!Graphics are amazing even on my mid-level system, my jaw dropped when I first loaded up the game. My laptop has a hard time running it though.Great pacing, lots of things to do; explore the solar systems, smuggle cargo between space stations, start fights with space pirates and steal their cargo, sell loot and upgrade your weapons...buy a new ship once you've saved up enough.I also like how you can customize your ship to fit different playstyles, there's no wrong answer, combat always feels intense and rewarding. Outfit long range cannons and missles to snipe opponents from afar, for medium range fightfights use blaster turrets and rockets, or cover your ship in lasers to cut ships apart up close!You also get to pick whether you prefer a huge tank-like ship or a sleek corvette, customize your speed and durability based on your play style.There are no levels, the more money you make the better ships and equipment you can afford, so buy trade items low, stock your hold with valuables, and sell to the buyers offering the most at the commodity markets at the space stations.One other thing I love is the music. Not only does it come with great music by default, you can use your own MP3 collection, and it will change songs for Ambient, Combat, Idle, Menu, and Space Station. So I made folders for each music type, copied songs that fit the mood into the folders, and added those folders to the game's music library. So when I'm cruising through space I can enjoy some low key Beck and Radiohead, but when a fight breaks out the game will start blasting Green Day or the Klaxons!Buy it! Don't even hesitate, don't even worry, don't even give it a second thought."
76561198027598348,Recommended,290300,25000278,"Posted: 18 August, 2016",all,MonkeyEmperor,"Apparently the developers binged on Firefly and Cowboy Bebop whilst listening to blues music and playing Assasins Creed Black Flag at the same time. The result? Godamn awesome !What you get for your oh so reasonable price is superb broadside based combat set in a really cool and beleivable universe. After receiveing a message from your Aunt to meet her at a rendesvous point you are given the keys to an old junker of a ship and from thereon out you are free to make your own destiny.You can take various mission types from stations, play the commodities market, Mine, Fight, run blockades to make a killing on Illegal goods and pretty much follow your own path.The Broadside combat is superb and made SO much better by the outstanding soundtrack. Fit your ship with broadside weapons, turrets, lasers, dumbfire missiles in whatever configuration you deem fit. All weapons have varying pros and cons with degrees of shield or hull penetration. Although the combat is on a fixed plane it really needs to be as I could see myself vomiting if I was trying to broadside in full 360 degree combat like in Elite.Your secondary weapons can be set to various fire modes dependent on their speciality vs different targets or just set to fire on everything as I have done at present. Some are better vs fighters and missiles, some are better vs capital ships.If you get sick of your space junker there are a nice selection of lethal looking ships all with their own pros and cons. This title heartilty deserves its good reputation so if you are looking for a fun and intelligent spaced based action game then dont throw your money at No Mans Sky (spit, eck) as this is a billion times better than that title will ever be."
76561198060340254,Recommended,290300,24705514,"Posted: 4 August, 2016",all,Comrade Commissar,"I never write reviews, and I only do so for games that I think are that much fun, that I need to tell everyone!Rebel Galaxy is a weird thing, it combines ""naval"" combat with space ships and quite some options to (role) play the game.The combat, is in one word, different. You fly in 2D space, as the rest of the capital ships do, and only the lighter fighters are able to fly everywhere, but you only fly capital ships.If you want someone to explain on how you should tackle the combat in this game, then dont read this, I think you should totally find that out yourself. There are some really powerfull combinations but almost everything works together if you set it up logically.In ways how to play the game, there are different factions.the Citizens are what the name says, these people just want to live and inhabit most of the stations.The Militia are a military 'police' faction, taking down pirates but also stopping illegal trading.The Merchant Guild and Mercenaries Guild are a thing of their own. The Merchants are traders and specialize in getting cargo through the system. You can join them if you want to focus on trading with stations, because the trading and goods system in this game is quite fleshed out!The Mercenaries supply contracts to you if you join them, also giving you access to better equipment, like most factions do in the game when you join them. They work with and against everyone, its up to you what you choose.Then there are quite alot of Pirate and Raider factions, you'll meet the Red Devils and Double Jack's first, and you can join them if you play your missions right and work against their enemies, though all of them start out hostile to you.There is alot more to tell, but you can find it out for yourself. I still havent beat the main story, as i'm to busy working for my chosen faction, which is alot of fun.If you can get this on sale, defenitely get it, otherwise its still a pretty good deal!"
