76561198032345700,Recommended,290300,18644213,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,RustyRobot,"Over the last few days, I have been enjoying this game very much. I have seen people raving about the sound track, and while it is good, after playing for long stretches of time, it does get a little bit repetitive. I do appreciate the ability to implement your own music library. This feature solves that issue.The gameplay is solid. The broadside mechanic works well, and once you learn to not shoot at targets that are too low or too high, wasting your charged broadside, you will become more and more effective. There is also an amount of strategy in how you approach the battles that you will inevitably be thrown into. If your ship is more maneuverable, you will end up using different strategies to what you would use if you had a heavier ship.I have seen people complain about the warp system, but honestly it is one of my favorite mechanics. The main issue that some people have with the warping system is that you sometimes are pulled out of warp into battle from enemies that will happen to be in your way.Theres a couple ways to avoid this issue:Scan before you warp – if you are worried about warping into a far superior foe, scan your environment (press “f”) before you warp out. The scan has as relatively large range. Take advantage of it.Maneuver while you warp – if you see a huge asteroid field coming up, don’t just fly right into it! Maybe turn left. Or you know, you could also turn right as well. That might work too.One major point, and the reason that I am writing this review, is to commend the developer. I had an issue with my save. I lost around 14 hours of progress. After messaging the developer through the forums, I was delighted to find that they are incredibly receptive and helped me resolve my issue within 15 minutes of my asking the question.Overall, I have enjoyed my time in the game so far, and I look forward to reaching end game on my current save, only so I can have an excuse to start another and try a different playstyle."
