,Recommended,290300,34722159,Posted: 3 September,all,- dan -,"Yar me hearties! Rebelsassins creed : black galaxy is described in the storepage as being a swashbuckling adventure set in space and this is very true, the game works on a 2d plane (for the player and other large ships) making it very similar to the ship to ship broadside combat in assassins creed : black flag and other nautically themed ship games. It was developed on a budget by a very small team and Rebel Galaxy is a testament to their skills. It features beautiful graphics, well designed ships, a decent story line and a fabulous soundtrack. The core gameplay loop is typical of space games (mine, trade, faction missions) and the random encounter system is a nice addition. While the game is very well put together it's scope is a little limited (which is a good thing overall) and once you have obtained the best ship and beaten the story missions there isn't that much for you to do beyond just flying around and enjoying the sights.Good-shows just what can be done on a tight budget if you have a good dev team-it's honestly heaps of fun and easy get to grips with-amazing soundtrack and it's also easy to add your own music files to the mix-looks beautiful-low price for what you get-better than star citizenBad-limited scope and once its beaten it's unlikely that you will be driven to play it through again-more options would be great, post game missions would be great, I would totally buy dlc for this-collisions can sometimes be... questionableIf you are a veteran space pilot then you might find this a little bland but for people entering into the genre or just looking for a more simple space game to play casually I think they will definitely get their moneys worth, I had a fantastic time playing this and wholeheartedly recommend it 4.5/5"
