,Recommended,290300,18626167,"Posted: 22 October, 2015",all,Pestilence,"TL;DRIf you like economics / 2D naval style combat / challenge, get this game.It's worth more than you're paying.Pros:This game feels highly polished for the ~$20 price tag.Economics function quite well, are not random, and you can earn Credits fairly quickly once you see the patterns. (i.e. if there's a Militia Embargo on an outpost, bring it military style products for a nice profit)The ships are interesting and specialized. You feel accomplished when you get the next awesome ship and throw some killer components on it.Computer requirements are well within reach for most PC gamers.^>It feels very optimized and lag is infrequent.The graphics aren't comparable to BF4 but, it's a very pretty game.The story, though not entirely compelling at first, is well written as are the characters for their minimalistic impact on the game.There's been ZERO glitching. That's just fantastic.Cons:Difficulty may seem overwhelming at first but, you'll quickly understand the importance of picking your battles and what upgrades are needed. Until you learn to broadside properly, high-range turrets will be your best friend.I can't really think of any others at the moment. I've been having a really good time. :)Suggestions:Co-op Play would be EPIC in larger scale confrontations.When on the Commodity Window make a sortable LIST of the other outposts you've visited and their pricing instead of the slow ""here's the price at this location"" rotation. I've spent far too much time just sitting in my chair waiting for the outpost i want to see prices for pop up without having to go back into space and look at it on my map.The distance between the sides of your ship and stellar masses when trying to warp is too great. Front space is wonderful but, if i can turn my Radovich completely sideways and not hit what made my warp stop that's a problem.Also, a question to the Devs;Did a few members of your team REALLY enjoy ""Armada"" for the Dreamcast? Because this feels like what that game should have been. I loved that game when it came out and put far too much time into it and this feels heavily influenced by it.Comp specs:AMD FX-6300 OC'd to 4.5GHzRadeon R9 280 OC'd to 280x specsUltra setting, Full Screen, 1080p = 140FPS most of the time."
