76561198042634433,Recommended,290300,21993408,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,ExploratorStavros,"I didn't know quite what to expect. But from the trailer it looked like it would be an absolute wild ride.It is.I don't know what pulled me in more: The incredible soundtrack, which while somewhat short, never ever got old and always pumped me up for taking on a whole enemy flotilla single-handedly while being completely out-classed and out-gunned. Or the visuals which are stunning from the very beginning.This game has hit a perfect spot of being scifi and western: a playable Firefly. It keeps you enthralled even after you finish the story. The developers really hit spot on on the idea of purely enjoyable gameplay. It's not complex and convoluted. It's not necessarily simple either. you have to think about how you approach your enemy. What weapons are best, do you go with massive firepower or shield and hull strength? A middle ground? How can a small cruiser take on a dreadnought 5 times it's size without getting obliterated?There are a couple pseudo-downsides, other than the (epic) short soundtrack,The first somewhat downside to this game is that because it's their first one (as far as i can tell), they weren't able to make it bigger, or the story longer. There isn't much character development, however they put a LOT of thought into what was there, such as if you listen to the alien languages, you can actually pick up what words mean what in the translations. I'm a language nerd and that scored MAJOR points for me.The other downside is that you have to get used to it not being a 'realistic' space game, since you are playing on a flat plane, you cannot do spins or attack from above or below as you would imagine being able to in theoretical 'real' space combat.But the gameplay is so fun that, at least for myself, i completely discarded that particular misgiving and simply had fun with it.This is quite honestly one of the best games i've played in YEARS, i can't recommend it more.This is one of the few games where not only do i WANT more, i NEED more."
