76561198069996606,Recommended,290300,19825060,"Posted: 21 December, 2015",all,Tech-Priest,"Well, I bought this on a whim, but it turns out, money was never better spent.All in all, I would defintely recommend it to anyone who's wanted to fly their own starship in a mostly lawless zone. If you've ever played Tachyon: The Fringe, you're going to love this game.I know that quite a few might be turned away due to the thing's lack of vertical flight. Put simply, the lack of a vertical axis isn't a drawback - it's a feature. The kind of ships you'll be in charge of, you won't need a vertical axis.I'll list out the good stuff and the bad. Hopefully that'll help.The Good:-1) Low-cost title that plays like a AAA game.2) Fast-paced and simple to learn.3) Quirky in many aspects.4) Great soundtrack, with an obvious inspiration from Firefly.5) Very nice ship design, and a used-up feel that's surprisingly cozy.The Neutral:-1) Star-systems aren't particularly unique, but the graphical detail and insanity offsets that to quite some extent.2) Trading and Mining are viable alternatives to a kill-em-all blitz, but it can be boring or tedious after a point.3) Fairly interesting characters, but their full potential was never realised.4) Cash is something weird - either so much that you don't know what to do, or too little, resulting in you getting outgunned.5) Mercenaries are a nice touch, but again - like the main characters - not realised to their full potential.The Bad:-1) Some missions can be hilariously broken, and tougher than they look, which can cause hair-pulling at times.2) Rather short single-player campaign.3) Can be slightly boring after a certain point, though not too bad.4) No further development on this title, it would seem. Hopefully there'll be more on this after some time.Definitely give it a try. You won't regret it!"
