76561197975404041,Recommended,290300,22819492,"Posted: 5 May, 2016",all,Stythys,Very fun game. The space ship combat is very enjoyable and it has a decent main story. Just wish the story mode was longer and they would come out with an expansion with alien ships in it.
76561197972321908,Recommended,290300,20190208,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,zyl0x,"Do you like Firefly? Do you like flying around in a ship and blowing stuff up? Then buy this game.Play as a pirate, smuggler, merchant, miner, mercenary, soldier or any combination you like!The story is nothing to write home about, but this is mostly a space sandbox anyway. The game itself is absolutely gorgeous and an incredible pleasure to play. There are many different ship types to play around with and different weapon combinations to keep you interested for a good while. The little dinky tugboat you start out with isn't much, but it won't take you too long to throw some bigger guns on it and start slugging it out with the bigger ships.Ship flight is arcade-style and takes place in faux-3D space: that is to say smaller ships like fighters and bombers (which you don't pilot) fly around in 3D, but the bigger ships, from corvettes to dreadnaughts, stay on a 2D plane. Ships have turrets and you can pick up a hireable strike-craft to help you out, but most of the firepower is concentrated in naval-style broadside weaponry.Difficulty is mostly linear and is determined by the tier of your equipment, not the size of your ship, so you're not forced to play a huge, sluggish battleship if you don't want to (or don't want to save up for it.) Some people have complained about the ""risk estimate"" for certain missions being a little inaccurate, but I haven't really had any issues with it provided I upgrade my equipment properly and am not afraid to bug out when the going gets tough.Default soundtrack is great - a pleasureable selection of hard rock music that fits the tone of the game. You can add your own music, or replace the whole soundtrack altogether if you want. Controls are smooth, with the occasional futzing required with overlapping cargo containers (protip: use your targetting scanner to lock onto the container you want.) Graphics are absolutely stunning and the sound effects are top notch.Definitely worth picking up this gem!"
