76561198030978104,Recommended,290300,18675731,"Posted: 25 October, 2015",all,Tylermcd93,"Honestly this game wasn't even on my radar mainly because there are so many space games on steam I generally pass them by. However this game was different after I actually saw some gameplay. It shares many similarities to games I love like Sid Meier's Pirates, Assassin's Creed IV Black Flag, etc. It shares that similar formula, there are many places in the vast emptiness of space where you can trade, take up mission for many different factions, etc. The economy is very in-depth but not complicated when it comes to trading. You can fully customize your ship with many different weapons and modifications (or even buy a new ship). Complete openness as well as many different enormous Solar Systems you can travel to and from. The most unique part of this game though, is the music. The music is very odd for a space, sci-fi oriented game however that just makes it even more epic with its t'wang of country or southern-rock-inspired music. I also have not come across any glitches or crashes yet. I would easily give this game a 10/10."
