76561197999455720,Recommended,290300,22165571,"Posted: 31 March, 2016",all,Andross,"Rebel Galaxy is a fun expansive space game that sacrifices complete freedom and dogfighting to bring something completely new to the table, which is fun and uniquePros:-Areas feel big and look wonderful-Awesome music which adds a bit of a Mad Max feel (my opinion)-Ship combat which reminds strongly combat in pirate games (hence swashbuckling adventure) which requires maneuvering to let shields recover or attack another angle of the enemy that's more vulnerable and using ""deflectors"" to absorb damage in an emergency-Fully voice acted with only a few quircky lines and many alien dialects-huge variety of weapons and defence mechanisms to choose from which can change gameplay, especially the ""broadside"" weapons-Possibility to either be lawful or piraty which will make some outposts hate you and others accept you-Trade or fight and/or join certain factions which have unique ships or items-You can engage Warp at almost any point and do not have to travel to some gate unless you go to a different starsystem-An interesting story around your Aunt and a certain object she uncovered...Cons:-You are limited to a 2D Plane, same as for the big enemy ships but not the fighters. Can feel limiting, ESPECIALLY when you have something thats below you, like an asteroid you want to laser to get to the goodies inside but your turret is on top so you have to maneuver in a way so that it reaches-Combat most of the time is just firing broadside weapons, managing your other turrets in combat is not viable-The camera is almost impossible to control unless you switch to broadsides. Game knows this and hints at it but it can take some getting used to especially during mining-Nearly EVERYTHING is automated. Meaning, for example, that if you want to engage ""Warp"" you have to wait for the game to give you the go ahead after you travelled for x distance. And retrieving a specific piece of cargo between many is really hard to do.-Controller is, as far as I can see, required.-The ""Warp"" will not get you to your destination immediately so you can sit back and wait until you arrive. Many time you have to almost drift out of the way of nebulas and asteroid fields. Its  easy to dodge but it can get annoying. If this makes the warping more interesting or annoying is up for debate. (I personally do not mind TOO much but I would want to sit back and let the game take me there without me doing anything sometimes)Overall: I like this game a lot. I played Freelancer and loved the heck out of that game too. And I noticed that even though you were not restricted to a 2d plane and it was dogfighting and not ship to ship combat in that game, I get a similar vibe from this game too.You DEFINITELY get your moneys worth."
