76561197993353652,Recommended,290300,20616775,"Posted: 18 January, 2016",all,Matticus,"Only a couple of hours in, and I have to say I am very pleased with my purchase.The controls are easy to pick up, and the combat is great with some sweet southern rock soundtrack. Like other people, I too shall compare it to the ship combat in Assassin's Creed Black Flag on crack and steroids, in space. Ship upgrades can be purchased through earning credits you earn from missions and the storyline. More missions may open up as you get more upgrades, and they are rated by risk factor (very low, low, average, high, and very high). You can meet up with people at space stations and talk with dialogue options. Dialogue options and missions you complete will influence whether you're good or space pirate. It's like a mass effect lite good and evil system, but I have no idea how much it will influence the rest of the game. No real opinion on story yet.My initial impression so far is that Rebel Galaxy is a very fun and very addictive game that you can lose lots of time to. If you're looking for something a bit easier to get into than Elite Dangerous or Star Citizen, enjoyed the ship comat in black flag, and are looking to also spend less money, then I think Rebel Galaxy can scratch your space combat itch."
