,Recommended,290300,32702856,Posted: 23 June,all,DARKSTORM,"REBEL GALAXY 2017 REVIEW:PROS:GRAPHICS: There is nothing like hunting and fighting your enemy while in the backdropof a stunning planet or blazing sun. All the ships going by and space stations absolutely glitter. The broadsidebattles are simply amazing and seeing the damage on your ship after you have won the batte with scorch marksholes and sparking remains makes you want to repair your ship and find the next bounty or mission!GAMEPLAY: If you enjoyed playing Freelancer in the past this is the game for you! Yet is unfair to compare the two as this game is quite different in many ways and is a hidden gem!The controls are quite easy to pick up and by just pointing your ship in the indictated direction of your mission (In yellow) the on screen prompts tell you what to do from hitting E to go to hyperspace for what direction your next mission is.BATTLES: If you think you will be flying a tiny ship think again as flying capital ships in this game is truly what sets thisgame apart from others in its Genre. The BROADSIDE BATTLES is so well done that at times it leaves you on the edge ofyour seat wondering if you will win. The ability to put up a shield for incoming fire and being able to switch guns mid battle is what makes this game so much fun!  DDG could have easily made this game into one that enabled the NPCs to just sit their and fight it out with you as you circle them and easily take your enemy out.Yet each battle can be unique with some running away and others defiantly going down in a blaze of glory. When you get to the 3 or four way battles then the CHAOS happens and its truly awesome!STORYLINE: If you enjoyed Freelancer and love Firefly TV series this is the game for you!The ability to choose your own dialog from being the galaxies ultimate Villain/Pirate to the goodguy will make you want to have two different save files to play good and bad.VOICEOVERS: You have to give credit where credit is due. We have seen countless games with scrolling dialog at thebottom that go so slowly our eyes bleed or voiceovers that make us cringe. Yet DDG did it RIGHT!Each character, from the local bartender, contact, enemy and every alien has its own unique voice and the ability to choose to tick them off or be their friend is a pleasant surprise. The hallarous responses are quite a blast.There is also a feature in Area Scan that pauses the game and you can talk with the enemy at times. (More Below)IN BATTLE: Quite a surprise is while in battle the enemy will at times taunt you or when loosing will contact you with different messages. This alone makes you feel when playing the game for the first time that your playing against a real person. GREAT JOB DDG!TRADING/MINING: Trading is quite enjoyable if you like to conquor the galaxy that way and mining changes things up from the usual gameplay.GALAXY MAP: Yes I gave this one its own subject and when playing this game you'll understand why. We are all tired I am sure of simply seeing dots and names on a map and thats it. Not in this game! You can scroll right in to see the area from astroids to space stations to give you an idea of what your jumping into. Again great job DDG!!MUSIC: You will see alot of comments about firefly in the reviews and rightly so, the music makesthe game and is epic. Then again if you dont like the firefly-like music and your not a browncoat than you can mute it.But either way from the moment you enter the game you feel like you could play for hours.CUTSCENES: Talking with the NPC either hailing from your ship, talking to the local bartender (Human, Robot, or Alien)is a treat and the ability to change your mind by telling them off or being the good guy is so much fun.AREA SCAN: Great feature very few talk about. The ability to pause the game and scan your enemy and see if they have a bounty, what they have in their cargo hold or even which one you want to target first is awesome! There is even an option at times to talk with the enemy through this screen, which will give you a cut scene to them either asking for money for them to leave you alone or to bribe you the other way. Great feature.CONS:Badly in need of a DLC!!GAMEPLAY:  Its been said in many reviews that side missions, random encounters get Repetitive. Yet depending on the player and if one is going from one mission to the next for hours and hours it may seem that way but I have found that it isnt really all that bad if you truly take your time and enjoy the game.I do agree with many who say that the ships going by are very few, not that we need alot going by inthe galaxy itself but it would be nice at major space stations and jump points to see ships coming and going more to get the sense that their is more than just us in this amazing world. (Ie. Ships coming through warp gates like freelancer)WEAPONS:  Being able to customize your equipment and weapons would make this game better and more diverse.2D MOVEMENT: Please dont take this next part as the galaxy being 2D for the game is certainly not that. Yet adding the ability to move up or down would be welcomed and would add another Strategy aspect to the battles.Conclusion: Absoultely an amazing game! Cant wait for a DLC and if Multiplayer did happenwell this game would without a doubt be on the top of the charts!! 9/10"
