76561197988293998,Recommended,290300,19542335,"Posted: 6 December, 2015",all,Wraithfighter,"Anyone that's played (or even remembers) Escape Velocity will probably enjoy this game.Rebel Galaxy is a fun space combat/trading/mining/exploration game, giving you a lot of ways to earn money and kick♥♥♥♥♥ The ship piloting controls are on a 2d plane, which may seem frustrating to some, but it's honestly a great decision. It makes the more chaotic battles easier to approach, letting the game throw more and more fighter and other small craft, backed up by larger frigates and destroyers.Story isn't bad so far, but isn't exactly groundbreaking either. More of an excuse to drive the plot along for the sake of the number of smaller side-missions around.Special mention has to be given to the soundtrack. Most games I play have me turning off the background music because I want to focus on the combat audio, but the western/southern old-timey music gives a perfect frontier feeling to the game. The SFX are great as well.Not a perfect game. At best, I'd give it an 8/10 (with 5/10 being average, damn it), and given the $20 price point it's more than worth it. But it's still an excellent first showing from a new developer. Really look forward to seeing what they do in the future."
