76561198013869979,Recommended,290300,18963046,"Posted: 8 November, 2015",all,RAUBZ,"Great game, especially for the money. Enough RPG elements with ship upgrades and lots of ships to choose from. First, there are some negatives: the late game doesn't offer much in the way of excitement, one you have the best gear, there isn't much that puts up a challenge anymore. It's fun to feel godlike when firing 20 broadside cannons and killing ships that used to give you trouble in a couple of shots. This wears out pretty quickly though and I find myself wishing they would throw more at me to match the level of my ship.Once the storyline is finished I don't feel there is a lot of replayability, there's no real ""other"" way to play the game except as maybe an outlaw, which will severely limit the number of stations you can visit and missions you can take.The positives, I think, far outweigh the negatives. As I said above there are plenty of fun customization options available to you and each battle needs to be approached with tactics in mind: lots of fighters?  Stay back and let your turrets work and fire some well-aimed broadsides. Big badass dreadnaughts? Take down their shields and get in close so you don't have to charge your cannons up and take them down fast.I haven't played a game with this much value for dollar in a long time, not being able to travel on the X axis isn't a bother as the game still feels big. Worth the $!"
