76561198025514459,Recommended,290300,18964889,"Posted: 8 November, 2015",all,Bender Sama,"Rocking Soundtrack, Great exploration and combat, and the feels of playing a game that makes me feel like I'm in the Firefly universe or something... In a word, Awesome. Will definitely be playing this one a whole lot. Also, the naval style space combat works wonders. Once you get the hang of locking onto targets and blowing them to bits it feels like second nature, and once you get a feel for it you will fully appreciate the inability to go up and down.  So if you're wanting a good space adventure with a fun combat system, this will probably satisfy. ESPECIALLY if you like Firefly. I'd say this is a strong recommendation.Gameplay - 9/10Graphics - 8.5/10Sound - 8.5/10Soundtrack - 9.5/10 (needs a category because it stands out so well)Fun - 9.5/10Controls - 10/10Overall Value - 9.5/10Is it beginner friendly? VERY, the hud does a good job telling you your keys, and makes you feel like a badarse pilot.Are there random encounters? Yep, you'll come across a variety of enemies and distress signals, sometimes fake signals.Should you buy it? If you've been looking for a good and simple space adventure to just jump into and play for a short or long burst, then definitely (especially, again, if you're a fan of Firefly or Space Westerns in general). If you aren't quite a fan of the genre yet, then even still, it could be a good starter point. The simplified gameplay certainly could help a newcomer to the genre find their legs and maybe fall in love.One con that I do see is that for some, combat may get repetetive. But as a fan of space and big guns, I did not find this to be a huge issue.I'd also like to note that I played this offline for a bit as well, so the Steam time is a bit off. Hope you guys found this useful."
