76561198175139057,Recommended,290300,18651783,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,ChubbyFatBoy,"I must say I am a bit surprised i'm giving this game a go. I found myself at the 30min mark having a bit of fun then stopped to play something else. Come back to it now at the 1hr mark and I realize something.....this game seems to be getting a bit tedious. I stop again to resume another game and come back later. Looking at the Rebel desktop icon I come to the realization that even at this early of a start I can already see how this game will get boring quickly. Without even feeling bored I can already see it coming. I pause and think and decide to give it the ol college try and make it past and still nope.Combat was ""eh"", mining I swear was going nowhere (and still don't care for it), trading wasn't a very good option since at the start if you so much as pebble your mighty ship was full in an instant and it all seemed so....not that epic? can't think of a good word. Literally came up on the 2hr mark and the time to decide if it refund or keep. I literally stopped playing for a day and pondered it because the game seemed like it had things going for it. Was absolutely lovely once I got the graphics settings right (gave a different resolution for some reason), combat was simple but effective, everything was flashy, the music and sounds were nice but it just didn't click. But I decided to take the leap and just go with it, and I don't regret it. I believe it was completely my thinking of the game. It's a relatively small download seeming more arcady and simple then anything so maybe I came in with a ""rush, rush, faster"" mindset. Once I put that aside (and a bit bored) I just pushed through and the game opened up for me.Combat although really simple can be as deep or remain as simple as you want it. With ships having multiple turrets areas it's completely possible to play it smart or just brute force a lot of things.  Set some of the turrets for specific enemies or bigger ship armaments with targeting priorities. Play the smart way with shield specific turrets to take down protection then batter them down with the heavy guns. Get extra protection with deflector shields and anti missile armaments because lord knows there will be lots of missiles being shot at you. Outmaneuver enemies and separate them for easy pickings. OR do like me and just go in guns & lasers blazing allowing anything to target anything in a blaze of bullets, lasers, explosions while taking control of certain ones when needed. Now this may all seem glorious and may be revving your engines and fingers to buy but as I said before, combat can be as simple or deep as you want. There's mining but I mean it's mining so it's not rocket science. Although there are ways to help produce better results but I have personally not dipped too much into it. I will say blowing up space rocks is flashy and hasn't gotten old yet though. Trading is simple and straight forward, buy low sell high with different possible events happening to effect said prices.At some point depending how fast you are you will be somewhat at the top of the food chain in not that long of a time but you can still get stomped at times if you get reckless. There are quite a few ships to get some feeling different then others and some unlocked later by doing or becoming apart of...things. Random map events, battles etc and small touches and details that I won't ruin. Overall I think this is a good game that hopefully gets better and in all honesty at some point will wear thin. This is no surprise as the space warrior can only go so far BUT the time getting there has been enjoyable for me at least. Getting that next ship, getting more turrets, better fire power, being able to go right into the fray just tanking everything and watching your lasers just shoot, blow up and just rip apart many a small ship as you focus on the big ones is a beautiful thing. Or just cruising paying no mind and seeing a kill happen all because an enemy got too close and looked at your turret funny.I believe this game is good and worth a buy and what can ruin it is coming in thinking or expecting something it's not. This game isn't ultra deep requiring big management nor is it as shallow and simple as it seems at 1st. The best way I can think of this game is it's like the ""Civilization Revolution"" of the lot. Just deep enough to seem familiar and can get you to think a bit but not so overwhelming to put off more simple people like myself (although I do enough a deeper game at times). Do you research, watch a few vids, take it out for a quick spin cause i'm sure some of you will enjoy it.ALSO! whatever you do, do NOT do swarm missions or things with the words ""swarm"" in them. If your not coming in prepared those ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s will rip you a new ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ within another ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥~"
