,Not Recommended,290300,20887458,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,Greg,"I really wanted to like this game. The premise seemed interesting and I love the atmospheric qualities of the music and graphics. The one big thing that I can't get past is the lack of a vertical plane. I was baffled that this would be a thing as the most basic of flight simulators have vertical planes and this is space we're talking about. Anyway, that lack of a vertical plane makes combat incredibly tiresome. These combat mechanics would be right at home on a tall ship/pirate simulator, but it really limits my interest here. Also, the story and procedurally generated tasks are a little too transparent and grindy for my taste. Overall, I'm kind of let down, but this game shows a lot of promise and I am going to be curious to see what they put out next."
