76561197977833737,Recommended,290300,18693976,"Posted: 26 October, 2015",all,BanthaFodder,"Think of a cross between the original Elite, or perhaps Frontier (if you're old enough to remember them) coupled with an amped-up version of the combat from Sword of the Stars 1 and you've pretty much got the barebones of Rebel Galaxy.  Throw in a distinctly wild-West, frontier ambience driven by the look of the ships (most definitely in the Solo-esque tradition of ""she may not look like much, but she's got it where it counts"") and the pumping country-rock backing track and you're close to what Rebel Galaxy is all about.The biggest single bone of contention people seem to have with this game is that it's a space sim that doesn't allow movement in any axis.  For me, this really isn't an issue.  The combat is deliberately designed with an emphasis on broadside-heavy battles.  This simply wouldn't work well across 3 axes.  As I mentioned at the top, combat in this is something akin to Sword of the Stars 1 on steroids - and for me it works beautifully.I would imagine that the greatest strength of this game could potentially be its greatest weakness: much like the original Elite, there isn't really a great deal of hand-holding; yes, there are storyline-driven missions to follow, but equally you're free to indulge in any of the time-honoured space-game traditions of trading, bounty-hunting or piracy.  From what I can make out, most players (myself included) seem to eschew the story and focus on doing our own thing.In terms of negatives; well, there is undeniably a 'grind' aspect as you're generally striving to get the next best ship or increase your reputation with somebody but as yet I haven't found this to be a problem - it's a mechanic that is always likely to be present in games of this ilk, as Elite: Dangerous proves.All in all, I think this is a brilliant, absorbing game that's an absolute steal at the price.  It puts many AAA titles to shame, especially, as if I've heard, the development team is only two strong!9/10.  Wholeheartedly recommended."
