,Recommended,290300,18704478,"Posted: 26 October, 2015",all,Chilson,"incredibly enjoyable, content filled and cheap space action sim. that is probably the only thing i have to say to get the right crowd to buy it, oh and if you liked AC Black flags boat combat and was bored with the other parts, like me, then this is an even better fit for you.the game is a bit grindy and can be repetitive at times, but the gameplay (which is AC black flags boat combat but in space and way better) is so fun and more importantly customizable. there are a plethora of different ships, weapons, shield types, boosters and other things i am sure i have not even unlocked yet that you can create anything from a super fast, manuverable smuggling vessel that can dance circles around enemy ships to a giant slow dreadnaught with enough guns, missles and protection to tear apart entire factions.speaking of factions....yeah they have no personality. this is the only negative i have so far and its actually more damaging then you would think. its a space sim where the different aliens, human pirates and militia all act and do the same things, even the pictures for each faction whenever you engage them only have two faces, male and female, in the case of aliens only one potrait. you will fight six broad categories of enemies, each of which has a different sets of sub group customizations. there is the dreadnaught, battleship, missle ships, standard cruiser, light ship and fighter from biggest and slowest to smallest and fastest. I often don't know who or what i am engaging until the name pops up on the ship and by then i don't care since you only have to care about one of two factions, the pirates and the militia. the reason you should care about them is because depending on who you make as your primary enemy will determine which ports are safe and which are not. this is incredibly important because ports supply you with all your needs from repairs to selling/buying materials for trade.the one positive thing about the factions is that they are always doing something. space is big, but even then i run into asteroid fields that are being actively mined by some korians or finding the militia fighting pirates and deciding whether i should help or not. hell the factions will even siege spaceports causing rising prices in certain materials and unlocking a host of missions from doing smuggling runs to that port for big bucks to destroying the commander of the siege in order to free that spaceport. or you could not even bother with the missions and go in to free the spaceport yourself by destoying every siege ship, looting whatever they drop, or abuse the fact that this port is under siege and buy all thier resources (which are incredibly cheap during a siege) to sell to a different space port for big bucks, and i mean♥♥♥♥♥♥tons of credits. there is endless variety and always things to do in this game.what really makes this game enjoyable is how difficult it is. the tutorial is short and sweet (even to short in my opinion), and after you get out of the first space system its open game. you could come across anything from 2 little fighters that you destroy in 2 seconds to accidently warping near 5 enemy dreadnaughts that use draining missles on you in order to force you into a fight that you will lose. be anything from a heartless smuggler, to a bloodthirsty, to even the peoples hero, the game makes a point that this is your story so do whatever you want. i cannot recommend it enough."
