76561197970939643,Recommended,290300,18665837,"Posted: 24 October, 2015",all,Grimloon,"Lovely little game, I thoroughly recommend it if you're looking for a simplified space game with minimal sim elements. The story is about as believable as Freelancer (by that I mean ludicrously cheesy but in a good way), it has an excellent soundtrack and is something you can mostly relax while playing. Well, until you go to a distress call and get jumped by 4 frigates, a command ship and more fighters than you can count! Ouch?I'd suggest taking a more patient approach rather than rushing through the story, the difficulty ramps up a lot between the first two systems so you'll probably want about a million credits to upgrade systems to be on a par with the NPC factions. Some of the best weapons also appear to be looted rather than bought (Viridian Beam? Oh aye! 3.8 k range and rips through shields like nobody's business!)Physics is out of the window, they never heard of Newton as you can stop dead then turn on the spot before almost immediately being up to max speed again. The weapon types seem a little limited but they do the job and fill the required niches, they just get upgraded to a new mark as far as I've seen but I'm currently playing the legit route, different factions appear to have some slightly diferent hardware available which you might be able to loot.Overall it's just good fun with a space/wild west theme that doesn't take itself too seriously."
