76561197969973054,Recommended,290300,22546665,"Posted: 21 April, 2016",all,Vonias,"So, Rebel Galaxy, this one was prettty interesting. First off the story does kinda suck, with all the random: hey your aunt has sent you this thing and now one thing is leading to another w/ you completing a lot of favors for people(and aliens)but just to simplify this review I will make a pro/cons list instead. so here ya go...Pros:1. THE FRICKIN MUSIC IS AWESOME 420/10. But srsly, this is what space cowboys will listen to someday... so cool.2. Combat (I'll talk more about this after the list as I have alot to say)3. Good roleplaying with the characters all speaking cool, differing languages its p cool and very immersive.Cons:1. the fact that the game is 2-d is kinda weird, personally, I think its nice as its simplifies everything for you(no learning how to read spherical radars, ship tilting, and confusing angles) but the fact that other ships can move on 3 axis and you can't can be hard to deal with as your guns sometimes can't hit stuff due to weird angles of engagement when a ship is above you. Overall I think it's neat and unique but its all just oppinion.2. Chores and distractions: again this is another ""con"" that im fine with. by chores I mean ""hey, go deliver this there"" or ""would you mind killing these annoying looters?"" that kind of stuff. I found myself unable to progress w/ the story cause i kept loading up on side missions and getting distracted by ""weird signals"". but I'm okay with that, I find it fun to just make laps around a system blowing up baddies, picking up drops and playing the market, but if you hate that kind of stuff, this game might get a bit tedious for you.Combat: Even with the strange design choices like only 2 axis', I REALLY like this games combat, if I had to describe it... hmm... you know old MMORPG combat, Like WoW or... uh... WoW, where rather than dodges and flurrys of attacks, its more about dps, health and well timed special moves? thats kinda how this combat feels to me. Methodical, and depending less on dodges and clutch manuevers, and more on having quality guns and activating your different weapons systems/ deflectors at just the right time. all while the gr8 music blares in the background. But, MOST IMPORTANTLY, know when to back off, sometimes one of the best tactical maneuvers in this game is to boost away from the fray, take a second for your sheilds and other systems to get repowered, and then re-engage, carefully using your cannons and switching sides to let your port shields recharge while letting your starboard take the hits for a while, and then activating deflectors at the last second to block a large group of missles.Sorry, I got a little carried away, if you couldnt tell, i LOVE this game, especially for only 20 bucks. I highly reccomend this.  BUT I CANT HIDE!!! WOAHOAHOAHOAH!! AND I WONT HIDE!!! WOAHAHOAHOAH YEA!!!*clears throat* sorry..."
