,Recommended,290300,25177810,"Posted: 27 August, 2016",all,Kyonko802,"This is the balance I was looking for between arcadey space shoot 'em up and intricate space sim with spread sheets covering the screen. Everything handles great, and the battles are loose and fast. On the space sim side of things you can spend hours mining and establishing trade routes between the space stations. Everything is procedurally generated so there's no established way to do anything. Item value rises and falls depending on what a station is going through. Food sells for twice the price at a station going through famine, and tech booms allow you to buy tech at ridiculously low prices so you can sell it later and pull off everyone's arms and legs.Mining, trading, pirating, privateering, assisting the militia, taking board missions, and outfitting your ship with the best weapons.Every second of this game is a joy to behold, and it is well worth the twenty dollar asking price.Oh yeah, I almost forgot the best part. The soundtrack. Just... the soundtrack."
