76561198112984827,Recommended,290300,27056680,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,Smitty Jagerman,"I will not say I don't recommend it because I certainly do. Even at its regular price it's priced very compettively in its genre and throw in the occasional sale? Totally worth it.What the developers have done here is great. It's immersive, easy to simply HAVE FUN with. A lot of work has gone into making this game run extremely smooth and it shows! From the mechanics to performance, balanced challenge to leveling up modules and finding just the right ship/hardware that suits your play style as you come into your own.HOWEVER, be prepared for repitive play.  It doesn't bother me much, well for the first 30 hrs worth at least but at that point I felt my money was well spent regardless.The game does have enough ""open-ness"" in it's universe to allow you to blaze your own trail, sink those long hours in just doing your thing aimlessly if you please or even completely disregard the main storyline if that's your preference.  So replayability and lots of hours potential are both there, in spades. But keep in mind the repition and whether it's an aspect you can live with or not.  Missioning, combat, travel, NPC interaction, tend to be very copy/paste otherwise I can honestly say this is a game world I'm glad to have taken part in!7.5/10"
76561197980109793,Recommended,290300,21046694,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,malloc,"Rebel Galaxy is a very nice space sandbox with a distinct wild west feel.While the story in this game does little more than serve as a progression vehichle, the game does much to let you write your own stories. Be a pirate or a law enforcer, or go mercenary. Trading and mining are also there for people who enjoy these things. Faction-specific ships and upgrades help replayability without being gamechangers.On the gameplay side, I've found it's easy capital ship flight and combat mechanic very satisfying. Having an essentially flat space never hampers the explosive carnage as you launch volleys of missiles, fire broadsides and maul enemies with your turret batteries - all in the same time. To keep things going, a splendid variety of random missions is available via mission boards - assasinations, assaults, patrols, escorts, contraband and trade runs to name a few.The technology of this game is not really impressive - no groundbreaking vendor-specific graphics here. On the bright side, overall production quality is high. Ships and stations are done with care, as is the bright and colorful galaxy, which is littered by nebulas, asteroids and junk fields.All in all, if you've got a privateering itch, but no desire to plunge into the depths of Elite or EVE, you should definitely give Rebel Galaxy a try."
76561198052405575,Recommended,290300,27047035,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,JackityPoo,679% more likely to exist than Star Citizen
