76561197970920251,Recommended,290300,26107209,"Posted: 18 October, 2016",all,gorkah,"I've got 4 hours of playtime on this PC and about 10 on the other.   TLDR:  If you like Privateer, Elite Dangerous, this game IS FOR YOU!!!!The soundtrack is a great mix of western, rock and really fits the game well.   The game mechanics just flow perfectly.  Instead of this huge 1,000,000 generated planets and open universe, they opted for a more gated structured approach.  Honestly, I really like that, BUT within each zone you have a lot of flexibility.It feels like Borderlands ina  lot of ways, where you can do main quests and side quests, any number of side quests and exploration, until you reach a certain major plot point where a gate is opened or a door, and then you can continue.So instead of borderlands zones, or wow zones, you have ""SYSTEMS"", and within each system, you have lots of bounties, stations, commodities markets, shipyards, planets, etc.  With a main questline guiding you through each system.Instead of player level, you have ""THREAT"" level, so if you go into a ""VERY HIGH"" engagement, it's like a lvl 12 Tauren walking into the barrens before you're ready.There is a simple faction system where you can earn rep, so as you help people you get ""CITIZENRY"" points, it's pretty cool.  I haven't played enough to know of any perks to this, but I'm anxious to find out.The gameplay is super simple, but has just enough bits to keep you going.  For instance, instead of a 1st person cockpit, you'll always play this in 3rd, I do it with my xbox controller and it's fun that way.  You can react to missle barrages with an RB deflector, you can turn to another part of your ship that's less damaged, prioritize tactical kill order of weapons.And in fact, combat is a lot like homeworld, in that you have to prioritize your targets, fighters, bombers, small craft first, then capital ships last, it's super fun and dpeneding on your loadout, you can either get close and broadside or snipe from long distances.So far I really like this game, it has a decent story, you can play it offline, customize your ship, fly around, trade goods, collect bounties.  It's basically everything Elite Dangerous is without a lot of the monotony and dull parts, but it has a story.So if you get bored with docking, bored, with FSD interdictor 2016, bored, bored, frame ship drive, bored, bored.   Pick this game up for $10, I like it more than ED and privateer for that matter and that's saying a lot.  The music, gameplay and feel keep me coming back, I'm glad I found this gem."
,Recommended,290300,26219407,"Posted: 25 October, 2016",all,AlphaOmega35,"I really enjoy this game--it's akin to a Firefly remix of Freelancer and Sid Meier's Pirates. The lawless vibe of the frontier of space is done really well, and the ships, planets, and effects are beautiful. It's limited to a 2D plane for capital ships (you can't fly fighters), which makes the controls easy. The combat is largely built around broadsides and keeping your shields and armor safe by rotating your ship, hence the Sid Meier's Pirates comparison. The story is pretty good--the voice acting is largely forgetable.Where this game falls down is depth--after the third or fourth system, you're only getting improved versions of your existing weapons, and there's only a handful of them in general. The number of ships is limited, too."
