,Recommended,290300,26925437,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,Lucent,"Lets get the bad out of the way first.This is not a free roam space game.  Much like free lancer it is level based, so as you go on, your tech makes the previous areas a complete joke, it also means new areas are going to be tough, but quickly get over run as you upgrade.Second, it can be a bit repetative.  There isn't a huge variety in missions, and while the difficulty changes in new areas, the activities largely stay the same.Okay, those are my complaints, now lets talk about why I even bothered to write this.The concept of a flat plane space battle game is kind of dumb?  Then you throw in the magic formula of capital ships firing broadsides and its just enlightening.  Ship combat was enjoyable in assassin's creed 3, it was even better in Black Flag, but here it so much more glorious as a giant space ship.  The feeling of boosting into a fight, swinging to bring your cannons to bear and just ripping apart other capital ships, priceless.The music is also very enjoyable and fits the mood of the game well. I've seen people compare the setting to Firefly, but I wouldn't go so far as to try and touch that legend.  However if the idea of a space cowboy in command of a giant spaceship enjoying a nice rock playlist rustles your jimmies, then boy howdy.I occasionally get the itch to play a mercenary space sim ever since I got hooked on privateer 1 and 2 years ago, this scratched it reaaaal nice."
