76561198031315605,Recommended,290300,24101687,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,The Wannabe Knight,"Rebel Galaxy is an excellent game made by an extremely small, but hard working, team.As many other reviewers have noted, this game gives off an unmistakable 'cowboys in space' vibe. From the (fitting) soundtrack to the bartenders dressed in clothing reminiscent of the wild west.The story, however, is slightly lacking. A few expected turns, and a tad too short, but still interesting.The gameplay itself is presented in naval combat format (similar to Black Flag) you have broadsides that deal massive damage, and turrets that passively fire. While some complain that naval format is lost potential for a game set in space, I believe it suits the game quite nicely.Once the story is complete, you've maxed out your faction ranks, and fully upgraded the ship of your choice, there is, sadly, little to do. You can explore, do missions from the mission boards, and look into the occasional signal. Other than that, there's little for the end game.I'd give this game 8/10, very well made with few qualms. You can customize the soundtrack with your own music, too. So there's that."
