,Recommended,290300,28421218,"Posted: 17 December, 2016",all,lellefot,"Now this is what I like. Riding into combat guns blazing with music blasting out of the speakers. So far so good. The game is very good, it looks good it plays reasonably well. I don't mind the 2D setting, since it would probably just be a mess in full 3D, like som many other space-games. The story is excellent and even if the ending is a bit on the low key, it does seem appropriate. The game itself gives you different ways to live your life. You can be a priate, a stickler for the law, or something inbetween. I will raise a couple of points on the negative side though. The game is based around fixed values in equipment. In other words if you have hull plating absorbing 10K damage, it will be 10K damage no matter what size ship you have. Same with weapons, and shields. This means that having a natural progression up the available ships gradually increasing in size, is in fact a terrible idea. This sice all your are doing in buying a bigger ship is making yourself a bigger target. If things scaled with the ships this would be a good idea, but as it is it's not, just find yourself a fast ship with good amounts of ports, and upgrade the equipment to max, and you're set. Second negative point is that once you've done the story, there really isn't much to do, the sandbox in which it is set isn't very varied, same type missins with the same type people. However don't let these things discourage you from getting the game, since it is still awsome for those 30-40 hours it will take you to complete the story, which isn't bad for a game these days.Pluses:Playstyle.Graphics.Awsome Soundtrack.Good storyline.Freedom.Pasting aliens with your guns.Minuses:Static values for equipment.Limited play after completion."
