,Recommended,290300,20072918,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,Jerkhappymatt,"Picked up this game while it was on sale, I probably wouldn't have bought it full price. I definitely would've missed out. This game is easily work 20 bucks, but if it's on sale definitely grab it. It kinda feels like if you mixed Firefly and Star Wars. The atmosphere and music screams Firefly, but the space battles definitely feel like Star Wars. I've only put 5 hours into at this point but I can easily see myself sinking over 40 with repeat playthroughs. The soundtrack is awesome but I do think it might get repetetive after a while, but the devs have it set up where you can play your own music through the game. Or you can play pandora in the background like everybody else. It's kind of a bummer that you can't fly up and down, only side to side. It's kind of good though, the devs did it to keep the learning curve for flight low so you can focus on shooting in battles. The actively changing trade markets at the different ports was a really nice touch. You can literally do almost whatever you want. Wanna be a space miner? Go for it. Wanna be a pirate and attack the innocent? Do it big. Wanna be boring and just play the story? Waste your money. The game isn't too hard to pick up and beat, but it's not a cakewalk either. You don't have your hand held in this game, if offers tips but doesn't stop you from running into high level pirates if you're not careful. That being said, it isn't too hard to earn money and upgrade your ship or buy a new one. Overall, I highly reccomend this game to anybody that's ever wanted to pilot their own space ship."
