76561198059673342,Recommended,290300,18945503,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,Anthony AyeDog,"New Review:It's been a few months since I've played (and beaten) this game... and I find myself passing up probably-good games because it just doesn't seem like they'll compare, even remotely. And here's why:Music: I fell in love. The sound of it, the timing, intensity, flow and quick pace is utterly perfect. When I'm working on something I'll still do a youtube ""Rebel Galaxy music playlist"" search and let it take over. I've recommended the same to friends and they all LOVE it.Combat: I thought it would be bland and I would hate it. I honestly only played for the capital ship combat. I wanted the biggest, baddest ship and that was my sole goal in the game. Somehow, and I'm still scratching my head, RG made corvettes and frigates astoundingly fun to play. I've gone from my big dreadnaught back into a corvette for no reason other than I wanted to zip and boost around a larger ship or through groups of enemy ships and spam broadsides to my heart's content. It's... satisfying..Dialogue: The trailer makes it seem cheesy. The game just confirms it. But it had a good story, I liked the characters, and nothing felt pushed, forced or too ""whut."" Great job by the voicing staff!Ships: A very broad selection to choose from, almost all with their own benefits (speed and size or firepower in terms of broadside ports, turrets, or a mix of both (I always preferred turrets.. pew pew all over). You couldn't own multiple ships at once and cycle through em at will, but the process of going from ship to ship (buying the next size one or trading in for a smaller one) was effortless, and smooth. On top of that, the ""grind"" was perfect. You look at the prices and think ""no way in hell can I ever reach that"" and before you know it, you're two tiers below it and it's within a day's reach. Great reward/price scaling!That's all I can think of for now, but DEFINITELY get this game, sale or not. And if you see that a friend wants it, get it for them, too."
