,Recommended,290300,22487440,"Posted: 17 April, 2016",all,rux616,"Disclaimer: I love this game, so while I am going to try and keep this review impartial, there's a very good chance that the application of rose-tinted glasses will still be involved.To start off: If you're expecting a full-fledged space sim, this is not it.  I would liken it more to a naval battle game.  In space. With lasers.  FRICKIN' LASERS, man.And it.  Is.  Fun.  Though it's not a super long game, it will still keep you entertained for quite some time.  I have about 56 hours on the books at the time of this review and I only just completed the game.  Keep in mind, though, that I took my time, did plenty of side missions, and have hunted down more pirate kings than you can shake a stick at.The graphics are pretty good in my opinion.  Good textures, pretty explosions, fairly well-designed UI.  Nothing much more to say about them.The sound though, or more specifically the soundtrack, is FREAKING AMAZING.  Honestly some of the best soundtrack music I have had the pleasure of listening to.  And even better?  They're all *.ogg files in the game directory so you can easily add them to your favorite flavor of music management software.  The music significantly enhances the game's atmosphere and gives it a nice Firefly-like vibe.The controls do take a little while to get used to, and can still be a bit testy at times.  However, once you do get used to them, you'll realize that things are actually relatively easy to control.I would say it's already worth the standard asking price, but if you can get it on sale you'd be silly not to pick it up."
