,Recommended,290300,20463659,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,MythicZephyr,"Finally beat the game after 32 hours. Not bad for a 10$ game (on sale.)I'd rate it a solid 7-10Pros:Solid Soundtrack - Honestly this may be the best part about the game, it really gives you the feeling of being on the frontier fringes of space, especially getting into scraps with pirates and crime syndicates and other degenerates (provided you aren't already working for them and taking on the militia.)The Ships - You start out with a barebones tiny 2 guns ship. From there you work your way up the ladder, selling it off along with whatever credits you have towards larger more heavily armed and armored vessels. The ship I ended the game with was roughly 10x the size of my starting one, with so many laser cannons and turrets I felt like I was at a light show.The Combat - The travel and controls are two dimensional for your ship, but that doesn't mean there aren't plenty of options to choose from here. From long range low recharge broadside cannons and pulse turrets to short range lasers and mine-launchers. Swarm missiles and Shieldbuster Rockets, and even an offensive deflector shield made to ram other ships. Your shields and hull will protect you in four different directions, and parts of the ship can be damaged if enemy weapons penetrate the shields to your hull. You can also hire a mercenary fighter pilot to accompany your battleship for as long as they can survive (though your combat ability will vastly outstrip theirs around 3/4's of the way through the game.)Cons:Grindfest - The most glaring issue I had with this game was definitely the amount of time it takes to make money in the earlier to mid parts of the game. New ships and components can be quite expensive, doubling in price for each tier up to the mk.6 parts. Also, if you aren't careful to be sure to upgrade your defenses before your weapons you can find yourself vaporized much faster than your weapons can destroy the other groups of ships coming after you.The Story - Not a whole lot going on here. You get called to the♥♥♥♥♥end of the galaxy in the middle of nowhere by your aunt who leaves her rust bucket of a ship with a bartender to give to you when you show up, only to learn that she's missing, and you're sent off to find her. I won't spoil the rest of the story that follows, but suffice to say it isn't terribly exciting.----All in all a decent game."
