,Recommended,290300,20463945,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,thrill,"TL;DR: Very simple - maybe a bit too simple? - but overall, great game with strong appearances of the ""one more mission and I'm going to bed I swear"" syndrome.WHEN TO BUY: ON ANY SALEFOR GRADES, CHECK BELOW.Technically, I haven't played this game for very long and I'm not near finishing it (I think), I saw plenty of the galaxy and the ships to be able to review this game. So, let's get right to it.BACKSTORYBasically you're a space cowboy, thrown deep into space andlooking for a family member.You fly around, do quests, build relations with factions, acquire credits, ships and new parts.There's a main storyline, but it's NOT breathtaking and you probably won't follow it anyways.CONTROLS - the most important part for meYou can use a controller or mouse and keyboard. I personally used the second option.You fly around using QE + WSAD keys, block incoming damage using SPACE, switch weapons with numerical keys and aim and fire with your mouse.The game controls alright, you need to remember about weapon ranges when aiming and firing, maybe it's slightly disappointing you can only move in a 2D plane unlike your opponents (!), but your weapons have a slight autoaim to make up for that, so you don't feel too much pain because of it.GAMEPLAYYou fly around the stations in star systems, do randomly generated quests that scale with the system's ""level"" and apparently how wealthy and strong you are, pew pew quite a bit, mine, loot, buy, sell and trade various minerals and equipment, where there's just enough of said elements to make for a decent variety.Some missions are way too easy, some downright impossible, but you can eventually find something for yourself.The game didn't take me away, but I come back to it every now and then. It has this charm about itself.GRAPHICSThe game looks fine. It doesn't explode with colors nor does it shock you with its photorealism, but it does look like a fairly new game, you won't look away in disgust, maybe I could complain about all ships looking exactly like stock models, no real differentiation between different factions so you can occassionally dumbfire at allies or neutrals.Also it's hard to attack and defend in battles where there's a lot of stuff flying around, but I'll let that slide.One thing I didn't like was the lack of the feeling of power behind every shot of broadside cannons. This game needs it.The game is optimized just OK - I have a medium-class computer and it never even stuttered. Seriously, good job devs.AUDIOSound effects are nice, maybe they could be a bit more intense just like the graphics, especially when you're using your most powerful guns. They are pretty good, though.The dialogues are copy-and-paste, all the same except for the main plot, repetitive and annoying after some time.Also apparently all human spacers are Southern Americans and Aussies. Interesting.The music is fantastic and fits the theme of space cowboy adventures perfectly, but, like pretty much everything else in this game, it gets repetitive and you may want to use your own soundtrack for this game later on.CONTENTThis is where it gets tricky. That's because I haven't explored the entire game yet. From what I've seen though, I'm only a few ships away from the most powerful destroyer in the game and about halfway in loadout, so I'll try to be credible.Systems are built differently, with different kinds of stations and factions controlling them, also with a different amount and kind of randomly generated events, so that's a pretty good job well done.There's technically quite a few kinds of weapons, but after looking at it for a while, there's a few weapons superior to others (lasers and missiles namely) and a flak cannon or dumbfire missiles for secondary weapons are pretty much the only ones that make sense - for defense or for offense respectively. So it's kind of boring.I'm heavily disappointed about being unable to have a small, powerful ship, because the strongest destroyer can just kill off a smaller ship in one strike from the broadside cannons. No way to manually avoid and a lot is limited by ship's size.VERDICTSo, how would I rate this game?On one hand, it's magical. It sucks you in as you start and you're guaranteed to come back to this game many times.It's pretty decent on the technical side, it's definitely not a ripoff and the optimization was wonderful for me.On the other hand, it can get really repetitive, boring, and eventually turn into a grind.Grinding is one of those things I absolutely HATE in most cases, but I'm yet to hate it here, so... Here it goes.Take the grade with a bit of salt, because I'm giving it credit for the ""magic"" I felt. Buy it on sale, probably.FINAL GRADE: 7.5/10CONTROLS: 8/10GAMEPLAY: 7/10GRAPHICS: 8/10AUDIO: 8.5/10butDIALOGUES: lazy/disappointingCONTENT: 6.5/10"
