76561197964589302,Not Recommended,290300,20833944,"Posted: 29 January, 2016",all,0xbaadf00d,"I feel like so many of these ""reviews"" aren't based on a playthrough. I just barely made it through the game, I lost interest at one point but then later I came back to finish it.Now don't get me wrong, it's not all bad.I got really taken by the trailer, the music, the ""Really decline"" - option. Turns out, when you see the trailer, you have seen all of it. There isn't that much music, not at least that good. And there aren't any real choices to be made in the game.All of the sectors you visit are more or less the same, each has the same guys fighting eachother. Even one that shouldn't have any people in it, because you are the first one to get there.And that moves me to the biggest letdown I had. None of the game makes any sense. I'v had Traders being attacked by the militia, which is supposed to be protecting them. I went the mercenary route, taking missions from the mercs was so random. There is no way to tell who you are defending and who is the enemy. One mission, you might be helping the pirates that HATE you everywhere else and protecting their dreadnaughts from a butload of trader frigates that have almost no weapons. Well, more free loot for me, since the trader ships are loaded.Which leads me to what the money and loot buys. The weapons, there isn't really that much to do. Each new level of weapon 1 -> 6 mostly just increases the damage the weapon. Ships are a bit different but nothing special. There is only one ship for each price range, meaning that ships don't have variants.The game really takes it's toll when you grind for that necessary ship/equipment to finish the main storyline. At the end, the game kinda suggest to you that maybe you should continue playing just to grind equipment. My immediate reaction was to exit the game.Oh and the story is nothing exceptional. I'll not spoil it any more, but don't expect anything grand. It's as bad as the story in X3.Ships are good looking and the combat can be a bit fun, but shallow.Should you buy it?Yes if you are looking for a simple space shooter game with some progression.20 euros is not that much, afterall. If it were any more, i'd say no.If you want something more, no. Don't waste your time.I hate to say if I recommed this, but I would not recommend it for myself, since I like complex games with lots of depth and tweaking. So no, i'm not recommending. But it doesn't mean that you won't find it worthy of 20 euros."
