76561197973152564,Recommended,290300,18774926,"Posted: 30 October, 2015",all,sofa_king_sick,"Rebel Galaxy is a fantastic spacefaring game for those of us looking for something more arcade-like than the hardcore sims available elsewhere.  I grew up with titles like the original Elite, Freespace 1 and 2, Freelancer, the ""X"" series, and my all time favorite Independence War 2.  This game is perfect for scratching that starship battle itch I get now and then without having to spend hours and hours (that I don't have anymore) grinding.  Sure, you get to follow the genre-typical gameplay loop that requires you to mine, trade, or take side missions in order to earn credits for better equipment.  None of it really feels like grinding, though, as even the most basic missions are varied enough to keep you entertained, not to mention the random encounters you may face on the way to said mission.  The 2D flight mechanics, though strange at first, fit the capital ship style of the game perfectly.  It really does feel like naval combat in space!  To tie it all together, the grunge-y outlaw rock soundtrack is the badass black cherry on top of the cake.In short, if you're looking for surprisingly fun space combat with all of the open world goodness, but without the depth or complexity (or price tag), of an ""X"" game or Elite: Dangerous, Rebel Galaxy is perfect for you.  This game is absolutely worth every penny of its modest $20 price tag."
