76561197973051477,Recommended,290300,18926671,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,RadRick01,"I had a really great time playing this game.It seems strange at first and I thought there's something wrong with my set up because I couldn't pitch forward or pull up. I investigated and realized that the game only plays like a battleship in space. You turn left and right but you don't pull up or pitch forward. I almost decided to ask for my money back but I decided to give it a few more minutes of playtime and realized I was really having a lot of fun. The graphics are awesome and the battles are great. You have main broadside cannons that are forward and rearward 90° from the side of your ship, and then small cannons mounted in various places that automatically fire at fighters. You can take control of the small cannons but you have so much going on it's better just to control the broadside cannons to take out the big ships you're fighting while you let the small cannons work independently on the fighters.There is definitely strategy that you need to use in this game. You'll find yourself suddenly surrounded and if you don't get out fast you'll be pounded to space junk. I recommend the long burning sub light thrusters. They managed to get me out of most tight spots. Make sure you always buy the newest shields, broadsides, and thrusters that are being offered as fast as you can.To sum it up, whenever I spend $17.99 and get 80 hours worth of fun, I figure I'm doing pretty dang good! It's totally worth the money!"
