76561198028059421,Recommended,290300,28430398,"Posted: 17 December, 2016",all,Buddytiger,"Rebel Galaxy is a space swashbuckling game, like the old privateer and freelancer. Instead of piloting the ship from the cockpit, it is from a sort of 3rd person view and the capital ships move and fight in a 2D plane, while fighters buzz around in a 3D environment with asteroids and debris. The game is rather simple, yet beautiful, with a thin storyline stringing together the different planetary system the player visits. The player is free to play as a merchant, bounty hunter, smuggler, pirate or mercenary for hire, or even a little bit of each... although a bit of imagination is required since all of the missions (apart from the main story line) are only made of a few lines of text: go there, do that, and claim the reward.Nevertheless the game is as entertaining as its ancestors. The music also is an integral part of the experience."
