76561198015947183,Recommended,290300,31637044,Posted: 8 May,all,firespectrum,"TL/DR: Tons of fun for its price point. It has flaws, but it's greater than the sum of its parts.If you come into this with single-player campaign version of Eve Online expectations, you will be disappointed. This game is like the naval combat in Assasins Creed: Black Flag, and I mean that in the best way. Your ship only moves in 2D, but there is action happening in 3D all around you. The combat is intuitive, easy to get into, and fun. Which is good, because you will have to grind for the good stuff. I reccomend grinding between main quest points. If you knock out the main story all at once, it will definitely feel too short.The story has an old-school PC game feel to it because it's mainly talking heads in front of generic backgrounds. It felt nostalgic, but your dialog choices don't have any effect on the story, as far as I can tell. You can mouth off to other ships in free play, which does effect your standing with factions. Given how simple the interaction system is, I really expect more story and choices.There are a decent variety of ships and classes, but you can't customize more than the weapons and systems you install. I can't even pick from pre-made paint jobs? Really? How far behind schedule were they?But all that said, the gamescape is beautiful and the combat is plenty fun for the price point. They NAILED the atmosphere of the game as a whole, which is especially impressive given that there is something to complain about in most aspects of the gameplay. It really is greater than the sum of its parts, and my biggest complaint is wanting MORE."
