76561198273190585,Recommended,290300,32464924,Posted: 15 June,all,Regelian92,"Rebel Galaxy is a futuristic space battle game that is reminiscent of Colony Wars 3 Red Sun in some respects. There are missions in which you earn credits to buy upgrades. Everything needs upgraded. The ship, the weapons, the hull, the shields, even the tractor beam for Pete's sake. You can explore dozens of different star systems once you have your jump drive. It allows you to use jump gates. You may want to upgrade everything to the maximum before each jump though. There is a story line that is original. You find an A.I. who has a bit of amnesia so you help her get her memory fragments only to discover a much larger plot. This game is addictive. The thrill of gaining enough cash to upgrade something keeps you glued to the screen for hours. The achievements are quite a rush. And you can choose which guild you want to side with. There is even an option to side with the pirates.There were a couple of things about this game that I did not like. First, it is completely inclined to the ecliptic. Meaning that the combat is not truly 3D. It plays more or less like a surface of the water naval battle. Enemy ships can go up and down but you can not. Secondly, there is lag. Sometimes when I am trying to go warp speed from place to place it freezes up breifly and sometimes it goes slow for no apparent reason.All things considered I would say that this game is worth buying. It is not a 2D game in case you are wondering. Watch the youtube reviews to see what I mean if you haven't figured it out yet. And although the lag is annoying it is not enough to really ruin the game.  It is a wild ride into the final frontier you won't want to miss. Addictive action, upgrades and an interesting story that you can sink your teeth into.  If you liked Star Wars and Star Trek then you will want to get this game."
