,Recommended,290300,33599707,Posted: 16 July,all,CanadianKeystone [no glasses],"EDIT: Note that like all games, this one isn't perfect either. I had a bounty mission spawn on top of a story mission, with a random gen bounty spawning mid battle. My computer didn't crash, but I couldn't see my ship through all the explosions and enemy fire.....EDIT #2: Some tweaks are needed. Like going to protect ships and having them open fire on you while you're in combat with their enemy, because the game can't distinguish between mission and reputation. :(I didn't expect to like this game so much. I almost gave up.The game is a little simple, but it's complete. And that's more than most games on steam. No Early Access B.S., just hop in and take the game for what it is. Be a trader. A miner. A rebel. A law enforcer. Be all of them.Few unique things:- It takes awhile to gain favour or lose it from any party - aside from how you start the game. So you can mess up, and recover easily enough. You have to actively want to be good or bad.- Regardless of your moral code - you have to abide by some rules, or your own people will come after you.- It may not seem like it, but there is A LOT of underlaying events/options happening. The game won't spoonfeed you all of it. I'm sure it's all randomly generated, but if you embrace it, it's great.- Market system is interesting. Buying and selling certain goods, certain places, etc.My favourite part is lets say you're cruising around, saving people, robbing people, etc... sometimes you'll just randomly get outgunned and have to run. Or you get met by a larger capital ship and get robbed, or die. I love there being a save feature, but only when at starbases. It makes it more real.Oh, and the visuals and music really add to what other users have mentioned: Style! Gritty. Rough. Dirt! Diesel! Truckin!This game feels more like a pirate game than Space Pirates and Zombies. And I love those games."
76561197980565224,Recommended,290300,33553136,Posted: 15 July,all,BpG Corbec,In the style of Escape Velocity and Privateer you are a faceless space trucker out to investigate the trouble an estranged family member got into.The game has incredibly stylish visuals and the emptiness of space is genuinely colorful. I like the feel of the navigation & combat as it is locked to a 2D plane and plays much more like a boat or mech game than a 3D simulator. This cuts down on the amount of controls and disorientation that would come with them. The game is generally light on unnecessary details and is an incredibly relaxing experience to tootle around in.The RPG piece of the game is streamlined as well. There aren’t ships or upgrades I would consider trap options. You can’t get stuck in a slow moving cargo freighter with no guns. Every ship is better than the last and when combined with the arcadey combat is a much more casual and action oriented experience than the many games that proceed it.The cargo flipping economic sim component is the weakest part of the game. Finding efficient trade routes and running them for cash isn’t exposed properly in the menus to make sound decisions. For the most part you should be shooting evil pirates during missions or in random encounters and just selling whatever they stole. Because all the upgrades are generally positive and cash flow is constant; money effectively equals exp and the game is paced well to provide steady improvement without the feel of grind.The music is fantastic. In the same vein of StarCraft II terrans you have truckers listening to space country. I think it nails the tone perfectly but if that isn’t your bag you can tie your own custom soundtrack to the audio queues the game uses for seamless transitions.Edit: I have completed the game and am pleased with the time spent. It does get grindy during the approach to the end of the game as you have likely settled into a favorite loadout. I recommend this game on a steam sale for a relaxing trip through space.
