76561198008335018,Recommended,290300,35184818,Posted: 24 September,all,Ironsights,"I write this review after having spent a decently long time in this game, for a single play through. I did not beat this game, and I likely won't...after having spent as much time as I have in this, the grind has simply lost its appeal, and that is sadly the biggest weakness this game has.Don't be led astray, and don't let yourself miss out on this game. It is fun, for a while. The combat is pretty intuitive, if some what simple, the story is satisfactory for what it is, and the game runs great. The issue is that if you are a story driven player, like me, you will run into a problem: GRIND. After 3-4 hours of good paced gameplay, you will find yourself horribly outmatched by your next mission and new enemies...so you fall back and grind for a solid 3-4 hours, completing otherwise pointless missions over and again to earn enough cash to get bigger better guns, armor, shields, ships, whichever it is you need or all of the above. Then you burn through another few hours of gameplay and then have to grind again...and each grind is painfully longer than the last. Personally, I am near the end of the game and faced with a final grind that would likely consume multiple nights...I just don't care anymore. I may come back and finish, I may not.All that said, I deffinitely got my money's worth out of this game. I had fun for many hours before it became stale, and I am satisfied. IF you are the type of player who enjoys the grind, who loves soaking time to get better and better gear, you may really enjoy this one. If you are simply looking for a few hours of fun playing Space Cowboy (or pirate, if you are so inclined) then you will not regret this. This -is- a fun game, and I do recommend it, you just have to know what you are getting yourself into. $20 well spent."
